{"cursor":"1384","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"Metric}} 'METRIC' (Mapping EvapoTranspiration at high Resolution with\nInternalized Calibration) is a computer model developed by the University of\nIdaho, which uses Landsat satellite data to compute and map evapotranspiration\n(ET). [http://www.idwr.idaho.gov/GeographicInfo/METRIC/et.htm Idaho\nDepartment of Water Resources - Mapping Evapotranspiration]\n\nIn the decade since Idaho introduced METRIC, it has been adopted for use in\nMontana, California, New Mexico, Utah, Wyoming, Texas, Nebraska, Colorado,\nNevada, and Oregon. The mapping method has enabled these states to negotiate\nNative American water rights; assess urban water transfers; manage aquifer\ndepletion, monitor water right compliance; and protect endangered\nspecies.\n","linknr":102,"url":"METRIC","recorded":1374778747,"links":["/w/index.php?title=METRIC&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=METRIC&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Metric_(disambiguation)","/wiki/Computer_model","/wiki/University_of_Idaho","/wiki/Landsat","/wiki/Evapotranspiration","#cite_note-1","/wiki/Native_Americans_in_the_United_States","/wiki/Water_right#Water_rights_in_the_United_States"